{"word":"βρέχω","slug":"βρέχω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>βρέχω</el></b> [<a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ fr.\">fr.</a> a root related to Latvian merguôt ‘rain gently’, <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ cp.\">cp.</a> <el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:βροχή\">βροχή</a></el>] ‘cause to become wet’<b><p class=\"pp3\"/>—<pp>a.</pp></b> of perfume <b><i>wet</i> <a href='B:490 7:38'>Lk 7:38</a>, <a href='B:490 7:44'>44</a>.<p class=\"pp3\"/>—<pp>b.</pp></b> of atmospheric phenomena <b><i>send rain</i> <a href='B:470 5:45'>Mt 5:45</a>; <i>rain</i></b><i></i> <el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:ἵνα\">ἵνα</a> <a class=\"S\" href=\"S:μὴ\">μὴ</a> ὑετὸς βρέχῃ</el> <i>that no rain should fall</i> <b><a href='B:730 11:6'>Rv 11:6</a>;</b> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ impers.\">impers.</a> <el>βρέχει</el> <i>it rains</i> <b><a href='B:660 5:17'>Js 5:17</a>;</b> by extension, <el>β. <a class=\"S\" href=\"S:πῦρ\">πῦρ</a> ϰαὶ <a class=\"S\" href=\"S:θεῖον\">θεῖον</a></el> <i>rain fire and brimstone</i> <b><a href='B:490 17:29'>Lk 17:29</a>.</b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:βρέφος\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:βριμάομαι\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}